channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Burgum and Vance Push Back on Media - Has Biden Cover-Up Caused GOP to Finally Say 'Enough?'
AOC threatens Supreme Court articles of impeachment over immunity ruling
item.description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez claimed the Supreme Court has been "consumed by a corruption crisis," and vowed to file impeachment articles.

item.title: Dems Rage at Supreme Court Immunity Ruling
item.description: Capitol Hill Democrats railed at a Supreme Court decision Monday that presidents have broad immunity from prosecution when performing "official acts." Democrats have long argued that under the Constitution, no one — not even the president — is above the law.

item.title: Kamala Harris' Shot at the Presidency Just Got Worse With Cringe Pandering Video at BET Awards
GOP Senate candidate ties opponent to Biden debate: Bob Casey knew
item.description: Vulnerable Democrats are facing new scrutiny over their comments and defense of President Biden's mental acuity and ability to be president for another term after a decidedly lacking debate performance.

item.title: Biden Camp: Immunity Ruling 'Doesn't Change the Facts'
item.description: President Joe Biden's reelection campaign on Monday issued a statement in reaction to the Supreme Court's decision on presidential immunity, saying it "doesn't change the facts" about the events surrounding the Capitol riot.

item.title: Which Joe Biden Is Mika Brzezinski Watching?
Biden camp dismisses Trump immunity ruling: 'Doesn't change the facts'
item.description: The Biden campaign blasted former President Trump after the Supreme Court’s ruling granting him immunity on official acts while president, saying the presumptive Republican nominee “thinks he’s above the law."

item.title: RNC Hails Pundits' Declaring Trump Debate Winner
item.description: The reviews are in, and former President Donald Trump overwhelmingly won Thursday's debate against President Joe Biden. The Republican National Committee posted a roundup of reactions showing people across the spectrum declaring Trump the winner.

item.title: The Democrat Replacement Theory Faces a Kamala Quandary
Clarence Thomas swipes at Special Counsel Jack Smith's appointment in SCOTUS immunity case
item.description: In a concurring opinion in former President Trump's immunity case, one Supreme Court justice questioned whether Jack Smith was constitutionally appointed.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Biden 'Hasn't Been Calling The Shots'
item.description: President Joe Biden "hasn't been calling the shots" in the White House, leaving that void to be filled by "a select few people," Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., told Newsmax on Monday.

item.title: Red State Democrats on the Edge! Alaska's Mary Peltola on Biden: 'One of the Smartest, Sharpest People'
House Republicans privately worry about Democrats replacing Biden: 'Changes everything'
item.description: House Republicans are privately sharing concerns about the possibility of Democrats replacing President Biden as their White House nominee after his poor debate performance.

item.title: Whitmer Disavows 'Draft Gretch' Movement, Relays SOS
item.description: Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer told the Biden campaign she's not on board with the "Draft Gretch" chatter that cropped up after what critics have called the president's disastrous debate performance and to say Michigan is no longer winnable for the Democrat incumbent.
